<HEAD>LaserPhoto NY14</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MINNEAPOLIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rock star Prince can't be faulted for lack of
hard work.
   Prince will barely be back from his European concert series next
month when he will begin his first U.S. tour in four years with a
pair of concerts in his home state of Minnesota.
   Prince, who lives and records in suburban Chanhassen, is
scheduled to play Sept. 14 and 15 at the Met Center in Bloomington.
   Then, he'll hit the road through at least Oct. 19, taking his
90-member entourage to suburban Chicago, Cincinnati, New York City,
