</TEXT>
<DATELINE>HONOLULU (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   One day in Hawaii is not Thaao Penghlis' idea of
a vacation, but the actor is happy that television work is cutting
into his holiday.
   Penghlis, who will play disguise and dialect expert Nicholas
Black in the new ``Mission: Impossible'' television series this
fall on ABC, said Hollywood has finally accepted him as more than a
``mysterious foreigner'' playing terrorists and dignitaries.
