<HEAD>Boy Fascinated by Pigeons Falls to Death Trying to Catch One</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BALTIMORE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 12-year-old boy fascinated by pigeons was
chasing them in an empty parking garage when he tripped into an
empty elevator shaft and plummeted 12 stories to his death, police
said.
   Keith Shipley apparently went with several friends to the top
floor of the garage Wednesday to catch pigeons, said Baltimore
police Sgt. Timothy Keel. He was stretching to reach one of the
birds and fell when he caught his leg on a short chain-link fence
surrounding the shaft, Keel said.
   The boy loved pigeons and kept a cage on the roof of his home,
his mother, Catherine O'Dell, said.
   ``I never gave him permission to do that, but he did it
anyway,'' Mrs. O'Dell said. ``He even hid a couple in his room,
that's how much he loved them.''
   When the garage was first built, cars were taken to the top
floors via a large elevator, authorities said. Because the top
floor was no longer used, the elevator had been removed.
