<HEAD>Eight Wounded, One Hurt in Gang-Related Attack</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Subs last 2 grafs, `In addition ...,' to CORRECT that woman
taken to California Medical Center. Also updates with her condition
and condition of other victims.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A gunman in a car opened fire on a crowd
outside a pool hall, wounding eight people in a gang-related
shooting, police said today.
   No arrests were made, and nobody could provide a description of
the assailant's vehicle, police officer Ralph Askew said.
   The victims were standing outside a pool hall in south central
Los Angeles late Wednesday when 18 to 19 rounds, possibly from an
automatic weapon such as an AK-47 assault rifle, were fired from
the vehicle, Askew said.
   The area is popular with drug dealers, police said.
   Wednesday night's attack apparently was in revenge for a
shooting of a rival gang member earlier this week, Askew said. He
was unable to provide any details of the previous shooting.
   It was believed to be the worst multiple shooting since the
so-called Good Friday drive-by shooting earlier this year, in which
13 people were hit, one fatally.
   In addition to the eight wounded, a pregnant woman was hurt
during the panic, Askew said. She was taken to California Medical
Center after complaining of labor pains, but birth was not imminent
and doctors were trying to stabilize her condition, said hospital
administrator Marlene Delp.
   Another woman, who was shot in the leg, was in good condition at
the hospital, Ms. Delp said. Six other victims were treated and
released at two other hospitals, but authorities could not specify
the condition of the ninth victim.
