<HEAD>Minister Pleads Guilty To Series Of Sexual Attacks</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Southern Baptist minister who said he often
watched pornographic films before raping women was sentenced to 10
life terms after pleading guilty to charges in a series of attacks,
prosecutors said.
   Gregory Charles Goben, 28, pleaded guilty Wednesday to five
charges of burglary and sexual assault and five charges of
aggravated sexual assault, Dallas County assistant district
attorney Mike Gillett said.
   Between sobs that made his answers inaudible at times, Goben
said his actions were the result of viewing pornographic material.
   State District Judge Ron Chapman in Criminal District Court of
Dallas sentenced Goben to serve the terms concurrently, Gillett
said. Goben will be eligible for parole in 15 years.
   Goben was a pastor of Outreach Baptist Church in suburban
Garland.
   As part of his plea agreement, Goben agreed to provide
authorities with information on other attacks he will not be
prosecuted for. He also agreed to submit to blood tests to
determine whether he carries any sexually transmitted diseases that
could have been passed on to his victims.
