<1ST_LINE>r a PM-BRF--DowntownShooting     08-25 0152</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Downtown Shooting,0155</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Pushing Cart With Possessions Shot, Killed In Front Of
Downtown Workers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MINNEAPOLIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man pushing a bicycle cart containing a
sleeping bag, duffel bags and a canteen was fatally shot in a crowd
of stunned downtown office workers, the second transient killed
this week, police said.
   The gunman, apparently a transient, casually walked up to the
victim at about 5 p.m. Wednesday, shot him three times with a
pistol concealed in a newspaper and fled through a construction
site, witnesses said.
   Several witnesses said they had seen the victim collecting cans
in the area, a trendy converted warehouse district.
   The Hennepin County medical examiner has not identified the
victim; no arrests were made, police said.
   On Monday, a vagrant was shot and killed in St. Paul. A
36-year-old drifter from Cincinnati has been charged in the
shooting, which police said apparently occurred during an argument.
