<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Cameroon-Rains     08-25 0111</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Cameroon-Rains,0115</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>1,000 Homeless in Northern Cameroon After Heavy Rains</HEAD>
<DATELINE>YAOUNDE, Cameroon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Torrential rains battered the northern
town of Kousseri, killing one person and leaving more than 1,000
homeless, Radio cameroon reported Thursday.
   The four-hour downpour Wednesday also destroyed 315 houses, the
radio said.
   According to the radio, floodwaters reached three feet in the
heaviest rainfall in 10 years.
   Most of the houses in Kousseri, on the Chari River just opposite
N'Djamena, Chad, are built of mud and have thatched roofs, easily
destroyed by heavy rainfall.
   A similar torrential downpour struck the town of Garoua on Aug.
16, killing three people and destroying the homes of 500 others.
</TEXT>
