<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Spain-Blaze     08-25 0138</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Spain-Blaze,0142</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Rescue Workers Pull Seventh Body From Fire Site</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PUERTO DE SANTA MARIA, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rescue workers Thursday
pulled a seventh body from the ruins of a distillery that caught
fire and exploded near this southern coastal town, a spokesman for
the governor said.
   The victims included the distillery's caretaker, his wife, their
child and three guests, who were eating dinner Wednesday when a
tank filled with 390,000 gallons of alcohol caught fire, said Juan
Jose Torrez.
   Rescue workers also found the badly burned body of an employee
amid the rubble of Alcoholeras del Puerto on the outskirts of this
town, 60 miles south of Seville on the Atlantic coast, he said.
   Four people, including three children, were hospitalized for
burns, Torrez said.
   Officials have not yet determined the cause of the blaze, he
said.
</TEXT>
