<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Spain-Animals     08-25 0160</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Spain-Animals,0166</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Tiger, Lion Killed After Escaping From Circus</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BILBAO, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police firing anesthesia darts to subdue a
lion and a tiger that escaped their circus cage miscalculated the
dosage and killed the animals, the circus manager said.
   Two tigers and two lions escaped Wednesday their cage via an
open door at the Circo Ruso in this northern city while an animal
trainer was rehearsing a new routine with them, manager Angel
Cristo said.
   Cristo said he and several assistants managed to return one of
the tigers to the cage, but the other three animals fled the circus.
   Police found the animals nearby. One of the officers armed with
the darts fired on the animals.
   ``Unfortunately the dose used to put the two lions and the tiger
to sleep was excessive, and two of the animals died from a heart
attack,'' Cristo said.
   The other lion was returned to the circus. No one was injured,
Cristo said.
</TEXT>
