<1ST_LINE>r a PM-BRF--RunawayTank     08-25 0180</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Runaway Tank,0184</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Tank Takes Solo Spin Down Residential Street</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RANCHO CUCAMONGA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A National Guard tank broke free
from a trailer and took a spin down a residential street, but
caused no damage or injuries in its 25-yard dash.
   ``It was the craziest thing I've ever seen,'' said resident
Debbie Trudeau. ``I was in the kitchen at about 3:45 p.m. when I
heard the tank's transport trailer hit the ground.
   ``I looked out the window and it (the trailer hitch) just broke
to pieces and the tank rolled off its bed. Then the hitch drilled
into the ground,'' Ms. Trudeau said.
   The truck carrying the M68 tank had left the freeway and was
traveling on a residential street when the tank rolled off the
truckbed Wednesday afternoon.
   The tank came to a stop without causing any damage or injuries,
said Deputy Chris Allen of the San Bernardino County sheriff's
substation in Rancho Cucamonga, located about 45 miles northeastof
downtown Los Angeles.
   The tank was en route to its home base in Colton when the
accident happened.
</TEXT>
