<HEAD>14 Drown When Ferry Capsizes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KARACHI, Pakistan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A small ferry boat capsized in a river
in southern Pakistan, and at least 14 people drowned, a rescue
official said.
   Sattar Edhi, who operates nationwide ambulance and social
services, said the accident occurred Wednesday night near
Hyderabad, 107 miles northeast of Karachi.
   Most of the victims were teenage boys returning home from a
holiday procession in Hyderabad, Edhi said. The small, locally
built craft went out of control when it was caught in a strong
current, he said.
