<TEXT>
   Filbert production is down sharply this year
but the nut crop grown in Oregon and Washington still is expected
to be the fourth-largest on record, the Agriculture Department said
Thursday.
   The department's Agricultural Statistics Board estimated the
harvest at 18,000 tons, down from 21,800 tons last year. Oregon's
