trouble controlling the illegal practice, the head of New York
Stock Exchange says.
   John Phelan, chairman and chief executive officer of the leading
U.S. stock market, called Wednesday for establishing common
definitions of insider trading on international exchanges in an
attempt to combat unscrupulous traders and reassure the investing
