   Aluminum Co. of America and Reynolds Metals Co. opened talks
Aug. 9 with the United Steelworkers of America and the Aluminum,
Brick and Glass Workers.
   About 21,000 members of the two unions will continue working
under two-year contracts that do not expire until May 1989. Since
