<TEXT>
   Stock prices surged Wednesday, bouncing back nearly three-month
lows. The Dow Jones industrial average climbed 37.34 points to
close at 2,026.67.
   The dollar was pushed lower by a variety of factors, including
central bank intervention.
   Bond prices fell in quiet trading.
   Grain and soybean futures advanced; coffee, livestock,
precious-metals and stock-index futures all rose and energy futures
finished mostly lower.
