<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices pulled back today after a big rise
in the previous session, as worries about rising interest rates
took a toll.
   But prices finished above the day's lows and trading remained
sluggish.
   Today's decline came on the first anniversary of the Dow Jones
industrial average reaching a record high.
   Before the U.S. stock market opened today, the West German
central bank raised a key lending rate and banks in several other
European countries followed suit.
   Analysts said the increases stirred speculation that U.S. rates
could also be headed higher. That hurt stocks because higher rates
make government securities more attractive to investors.
